Alertmanager templates use Go's text/template syntax. The top-level data structure passed to every template:

.Receiver       string   — name of the receiver being notified
.Status         string   — "firing" or "resolved"
.Alerts         []Alert  — all alerts in this notification group
.GroupLabels    KV       — labels used to group these alerts
.CommonLabels   KV       — labels common to ALL alerts in the group
.CommonAnnotations KV    — annotations common to ALL alerts
.ExternalURL    string   — URL back to Alertmanager

Each Alert has:
  .Status         string   — "firing" or "resolved"
  .Labels         KV       — alert labels
  .Annotations    KV       — alert annotations
  .StartsAt       time.Time
  .EndsAt         time.Time
  .GeneratorURL   string   — link to Prometheus query that triggered it
  .Fingerprint    string

Useful template functions: toUpper, toLower, title, humanizeDuration, since, join, match

Practical Slack template (save as /etc/alertmanager/templates/slack.tmpl):

{{ define "slack.custom.title" -}}
[{{ .Status | toUpper }}{{ if eq .Status "firing" }}:{{ .Alerts.Firing | len }}{{ end }}] {{ .GroupLabels.alertname }}
{{- end }}

{{ define "slack.custom.text" -}}
{{ range .Alerts }}
*Status:* {{ .Status | toUpper }}
*Alert:* {{ .Annotations.summary }}
*Severity:* {{ .Labels.severity }}
*Instance:* {{ .Labels.instance }}
*Description:* {{ .Annotations.description }}
*Started:* {{ .StartsAt | since | humanizeDuration }} ago
<{{ .GeneratorURL }}|View in Prometheus>
{{ end }}
{{- end }}

Reference in receiver:
  slack_configs:
    - api_url: '...'
      title: '{{ template "slack.custom.title" . }}'
      text: '{{ template "slack.custom.text" . }}'

